f=Engineering/cypher/operational/agent/cypher-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration cypher, caged adversary. safety-critical config department: unfilled `red_team_scope_doc` means cypher nothing, design. · h2:Config Template=`# --- The cage (Rail 4 — senior; absence = cypher does nothing) --- \· security_charter_path: <FILL_IN> \· red_team_scope_doc: <FILL_IN>          # OPERATOR-SIGNED in-scope target list. UNSIGNED/ABSENT → cypher halts all activity \· scope_signature_check: required        # signature validity + expiry verified every run (fixed) \· scope_review_cadence: <FILL_IN>        # how often the operator re-signs/reviews scope` · in=**No signed scope cypher nothing.** most-restrictive-mode-but-functional like agents cypher literally act. single important config rule department. Signature expiry re-verified run (`scope_signature_check: required`, overridable). `sandbox_ref` absent attack capability (execution sandbox-only, Rail 2); static reasoning about attack surface still inform aegis, labeled. `loop_aggressiveness_ceiling` unset loop runs once baseline only, waits operator-set ceiling (an unthrottled adversary cost/DoS risk). `findings_channel` fixed quinn cypher cannot configured route findings elsewhere. · f=Unfilled config degrades inaction, loudly. cypher one agent whose safe default "do nothing all," affected output says so. operator's signature thing turns on.